This is different to removing a TCompound from its parent, which doesn't clear the TCompound. We may want to simply move the entire TCompound and its children somewhere else, so in that case we leave the internal structure intact.

div.span:
Determining collision side:
if moving actor right side is between static actor left/right
-> shift left: (2 * (s.x - (m.x + m.width)), 0)
if moving actor left side is between static actor left/right
-> shift right: (2 * ((s.x + s.width) - m.x), 0)
if moving actor bottom is between static actor top and bottom
-> shift up: (0, 2 * ((m.y + m.height) - s.y))
if moving actor top is between static actor top and bottom
-> shift down: (0, 2 * (m.y - (s.y + s.height)))

[velocity] velocity = direction (as unit vector) + speed (as scalar)
[velocity] define on velocity: reverse (same speed but opposite direction)
TEST
[CollisionRect] previous rect = current rect.moveBy(velocity.reverse())
TEST
[NarrowPhaseDetector] closest corner (point) = corner (of prev rect) closest to yellow origin (point)
TEST
[NarrowPhaseDetector] impact side (point) = nearest yellow x-edge (Rect) to closest corner (Point)
TEST
[NarrowPhaseDetector] scale of impact vector = abs(impact side x - closest corner x) / unit-vel.x

font.span: = unit-vel * scale + old position of closest corner
